\pard\qc\sa240\f0\fs34\b Know Me Tab Update One-Pager\b0\par
\pard\qc\sa280\f0\fs20\cf7 Mission Critical Services Unified Portal | March 2026\cf0\par

\pard\sa160\f0\fs22\b Executive Summary\b0\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs22 The Know Me tab has been repositioned from a customer profile page into a service decision page. The updated design helps teams understand service risk, operational pressure, ownership, and next actions in one place instead of forcing them to gather signals from CRM, support views, Power BI, and ADO separately.\par

\pard\sa140\f0\fs22\b The update focused on three outcomes:\b0\par
\pard\li360\sa100\fs22\bullet\tab Reduce noise and remove profile-style content that does not change delivery behavior\par
\pard\li360\sa100\fs22\bullet\tab Bring current service and backlog signals into the page through Power BI insights\par
\pard\li360\sa220\fs22\bullet\tab Add onboarding readiness context so teams can see pre-onboarding risk before it becomes a support problem\par

\pard\sa180\f0\fs22\b 1. What Changed\b0\par

